{"word":"παιδάριον","slug":"παιδάριον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παιδάριον</b></el> <el>(πᾰιδάριον, ου, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Diminutive'>Dim.</a> of <a href='S:παῖς'><el>παῖς</el></a>\n<p/><i>a young, little boy</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>ἐκ παιδαρίου</el> from <i>a child</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>young children</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: <i>a young slave</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/>"}]}